      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\swift\ring_specifications.dita" xtrc="li:14;300:11">For a given partition power, the minimum number of drives results in approximately 10,000
        partition directories per drive. With more directories on a drive results in performance
        issues.</li>
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\swift\ring_specifications.dita" xtrc="li:15;303:11">
        <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\swift\ring_specifications.dita" xtrc="p:25;304:12">For a given partition power, the maximum number of drives results in approximately 10
          partition directories per drive. With fewer directories per drive results in an uneven
          distribution of space utilization.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\swift\ring_specifications.dita" xtrc="p:26;309:8"> It is easy to select an appropriate partition power if your system is a fixed size. Select a
